'''Dhareru''' is a village in Bhiwani Tehsil in the [[Bhiwani district]] of the Indian state of Haryana. Part of the [[Hisar division]], it is located {{Convert|14|km|mi}} east of the district headquarters of [[Bhiwani]]. It lies {{Convert|13|km|mi}} from Bhiwani and {{Convert|266|km|mi}} from the state capital, [[Chandigarh]]. Its primary post office is Manheru.

==Demographics==

As of [[2011 census of India|2011 India census]], Dhareru has a population of 5,491 and 942 households. Males (2,956) constitute 53.83%  of the population and females (2,535) 46.16%. Dhareru  has an average literacy (3,480) rate of 63.37%, which is lower than the national average of 74%; male literacy (2,113) is 60.71%, and female literacy (1,367) is 39.28% of total literates. In Dhareru, 13.71% of the population is under 6 years of age (753).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/pca/SearchDetails.aspx?Id=62803|title=Census of India 2011|accessdate=29 April 2014}}</ref>

